----   Set up a new Mac System For Development ----- Note to myself
1) Download  and install Chrome https://www.google.com/chrome
2) Install Magnet for Window Management https://itunes.apple.com/gr/app/magnet/id441258766?mt=12&ign-mpt=uo%3D4
3) Install Brew https://brew.sh/
4) Assign Basic Fn keys :Settings keyboard shortcut F2 Focus on menu bar, F3 focus dock, F4 next active window


--- GIT ----
ssh-keygen -t rsa -C "kabasakalis@gmail.com"
Copy the contents of the public key on my github and bitbucket

--- ZSH ----
Keep it simple, skip the script in dotfiles and just:

brew install coreutils
brew install zsh zsh-completions
Run zsh for default configuration
Copy the following line to .zshrc
fpath=(/usr/local/share/zsh-completions $fpath)
Install oh-my-zsh
curl -L https://github.com/robbyrussell/oh-my-zsh/raw/master/tools/install.sh | sh
Switch shell from bash to zsh
chsh -s /bin/zsh

---INSTALL POWERLINE FONTS FOR ZSH  ---
Download and install Powerline fonts
https://github.com/powerline/fonts
cd fonts && install.sh

 -- DEVICONS FOR NEOVIM ---
 Make sure neovim/plugins contains
Plug 'ryanoasis/vim-devicons'
Install Nerd fonts simply with

brew tap caskroom/fonts
brew cask install font-hack-nerd-font

See https://github.com/ryanoasis/nerd-fonts#font-installation

# Add in .bashrc to make zsh default shell
# Launch Zsh in .bachrc
if [ -t 1 ]; then
exec zsh
fi

-- INSTALL NEOVIM ---
brew install neovim


-- Install Essential gems: ---
gem install rubocop rubocop-rspec starscope ruby-beautify haml-lint scss-lint mdl neovim && npm install js-beautify && install exuberant-ctags && install xclip rcodetools

-- sudo gem install tmuxinator


-- PYTHON  (ensure neovim has proper python environment --
brew install python (version 3)
brew install python@2 (version 2)

pip3 install \
